WEBVTT

1
00:00:12.426 --> 00:00:18.327
Traditional prescriptions for growth in Africa are not working very well.
传统的经济增长手段在非洲并非那么管用。

2
00:00:18.339 --> 00:00:24.919
After one trillion dollars in African development-related aid in the last 60 years,
尽管在过去的60年里，非洲获得了过万亿美元的经济援助，

3
00:00:24.919 --> 00:00:29.667
real per capita income today is lower than it was in the 1970s.
如今实际的人均收入比上世纪70年代还要低。

4
00:00:30.687 --> 00:00:32.990
Aid is not doing too well.
援助并没有太大的帮助。

5
00:00:32.990 --> 00:00:34.408
In response,
对此，

6
00:00:34.408 --> 00:00:38.492
the Bretton Woods institutions -- the IMF and the World Bank --
布雷顿森林体系－国际货币基金组织和世界银行

7
00:00:38.492 --> 00:00:42.046
pushed for free trade not aid,
推崇自由贸易，而不是经济援助，

8
00:00:42.046 --> 00:00:46.271
yet the historical record shows little empirical evidence
然而历史数据表明，

9
00:00:43.859 --> 00:00:49.961
that free trade leads to economic growth.
没有实质证据证明自由贸易会促进非洲的经济增长。

10
00:00:50.381 --> 00:00:54.280
The newly prescribed  silver bullet is microcredit.
最新的经济增长手段是"小额贷款”。

11
00:00:54.280 --> 00:00:57.997
We seem to be fixated on this romanticized idea
我们的想法似乎过分浪漫，

12
00:00:57.997 --> 00:01:01.851
that every poor peasant in Africa is an entrepreneur.
以为所有非洲贫农都是创业家。

13
00:01:01.851 --> 00:01:03.918
(Laughter)
（笑声）

14
00:01:05.148 --> 00:01:10.518
Yet my work and travel in 40-plus countries across Africa
然而，在非洲40多个国家的工作和旅途的经验告诉我，

15
00:01:10.518 --> 00:01:15.435
have taught me that most people want jobs instead.
大多数人民想要的只是就业。

16
00:01:15.435 --> 00:01:18.570
My solution: Forget micro-entrepreneurs.
我（对促进经济增长）的方案是：且将小额贷款放一边。

17
00:01:19.010 --> 00:01:22.656
Let's invest in building pan-African titans
让我们投资构建泛非洲的“巨无霸” （大型企业）

18
00:01:22.656 --> 00:01:26.881
like Sudanese businessman Mo Ibrahim.
如苏丹的企业家——易卜拉欣（Mo Ibrahim）

19
00:01:26.881 --> 00:01:32.779
Mo took a contrarian bet on Africa when he founded Celtel International in '98
1998年，易卜拉欣在非洲逆势而为，成立了Celtel国际公司，

20
00:01:32.779 --> 00:01:36.314
and built it into a mobile  cellular provider
并将其打造成移动运营商。

21
00:01:36.314 --> 00:01:42.721
with 24 million subscribers across 14 African countries by 2004.
2004年，Celtel 已有2400万用户，服务覆盖非洲14个国家。

22
00:01:43.896 --> 00:01:47.565
The Mo model might be better than the everyman entrepreneur model,
相比于“人人都是创业家” 的模式，易卜拉欣的创业模式也许较优。

23
00:01:47.565 --> 00:01:51.561
which prevents an effective means of diffusion and knowledge-sharing.
因为大众创业模式阻碍了有效的融合手段和知识共享。

24
00:01:51.561 --> 00:01:54.177
Perhaps we are not at a stage in Africa
或许，在非洲目前所处阶段，

25
00:01:54.177 --> 00:01:59.444
where many actors and small enterprises leads to growth through competition.
经济增长不是靠大量个体和小型企业竞争而取得。

26
00:01:59.444 --> 00:02:02.854
Consider these two alternative scenarios.
考虑以下两个不同的情景：

27
00:02:02.854 --> 00:02:08.890
One: You loan 200 dollars  to each of 500 banana farmers
情景一：你给种植香蕉的500个农民每人贷200美元，

28
00:02:08.890 --> 00:02:11.787
allowing them to dry  their surplus bananas
让他们可以干燥处理剩余的香蕉，

29
00:02:11.787 --> 00:02:16.115
and fetch 15 percent more revenue at the local market.
在当地市场获得15%的收入增长。

30
00:02:16.115 --> 00:02:22.297
Or two: You give 100,000 dollars to one savvy entrepreneur
情景二：你把10万美元给一个精明的企业家，

31
00:02:22.297 --> 00:02:27.515
and help her set up a factory that yields 40 percent additional income
帮助她建造一个工厂，足以给那500个种植香蕉的农民，

32
00:02:27.515 --> 00:02:32.612
to all 500 banana farmers and creates 50 additional jobs.
带来额外40%的收入，同时又创造了50个就业岗位。

33
00:02:33.567 --> 00:02:36.191
We invested in the second scenario,
我们选择了后者，

34
00:02:36.191 --> 00:02:40.687
and backed 26-year-old Kenyan entrepreneur Eric Muthomi
向一位26岁的肯尼亚企业家，Eric Muthomi 给予了投资，

35
00:02:40.687 --> 00:02:44.356
to set up an agro-processing factory called Stawi
帮助他设立Stawi农产品加工厂。

36
00:02:44.356 --> 00:02:49.240
to produce gluten-free banana-based flour and baby food.
该加工厂专门生产无麸质的以香蕉为主的面粉和婴儿食品。

37
00:02:50.062 --> 00:02:53.103
Stawi is leveraging economies of scale
Stawi借助规模经济效应采用现代加工生产模式，

38
00:02:53.103 --> 00:02:57.984
and using modern manufacturing processes to create value for not only its owners
不仅为工厂老板创造了价值，

39
00:02:57.984 --> 00:03:01.319
but its workers, who have an ownership in the business.
还为持有股份的员工创造了价值。

40
00:03:02.399 --> 00:03:08.528
Our dream is to take an Eric Muthomi and try to help him become a Mo Ibrahim,
我们的梦想是帮助 Eric Muthomi，让他成为又一位 “易卜拉欣 “。

41
00:03:08.528 --> 00:03:13.675
which requires skill, financing, local and global partnerships,
这一梦想的实现，需要技术、资金、地区与全球范围的合作、

42
00:03:13.675 --> 00:03:16.345
and extraordinary perseverance.
以及非凡的毅力。

43
00:03:16.345 --> 00:03:18.430
But why pan-African?
但是，为什么选择泛非洲？

44
00:03:19.410 --> 00:03:24.008
The scramble for Africa during the Berlin Conference of 1884 --
1884年的柏林会议上对非洲的争夺，

45
00:03:24.008 --> 00:03:28.744
where, quite frankly, we Africans were not exactly consulted --
——实话说，我们非洲人民的意见就没有被征询过——

46
00:03:28.744 --> 00:03:34.152
(Laughter) (Applause) --
（笑声）（掌声）

47
00:03:35.362 --> 00:03:37.823
resulted in massive fragmentation
这导致了非洲大规模的“碎片化”，

48
00:03:37.823 --> 00:03:40.354
and many sovereign states with small populations:
产生了许多人口较少的主权国家：

49
00:03:40.354 --> 00:03:43.396
Liberia, four million; Cape Verde, 500,000.
利比里亚，400万人口；佛得角，50万人口。

50
00:03:43.396 --> 00:03:46.135
Pan-Africa gives you one billion people,
泛非洲有10亿人口，

51
00:03:46.135 --> 00:03:50.292
granted across 55 countries with trade barriers and other impediments,
横跨了55个国家，还有各种贸易壁垒和其它障碍。

52
00:03:50.292 --> 00:03:53.525
but our ancestors traded across the continent
不过，在欧洲列强争夺非洲、划下国界前，

53
00:03:53.525 --> 00:03:56.102
before Europeans drew lines around us.
我们的祖先在非洲大陆到处进行贸易。

54
00:03:56.102 --> 00:03:59.539
The pan-African opportunities outweigh the challenges,
泛非洲的机遇大于挑战，

55
00:03:59.539 --> 00:04:02.975
and that's why we're expanding Stawi's markets from just Kenya
因此，我们从肯尼亚开始将 Stawi的市场扩张到阿尔及利亚、

56
00:04:02.975 --> 00:04:07.340
to Algeria, Nigeria, Ghana, and anywhere else that will buy our food.
尼日利亚、加纳，还有所有会购买我们的食物的地方。

57
00:04:07.340 --> 00:04:11.334
We hope to help solve food security, empower farmers, create jobs,
我们希望帮助解决食品安全问题，改善农民生活，创造就业机会，

58
00:04:10.664 --> 00:04:15.768
develop the local economy, and we hope to become rich in the process.
发展当地经济，并在此历程中致富。

59
00:04:15.768 --> 00:04:17.987
While it's not the sexiest approach,
也许这不是最鲜嫩欲滴的手段，

60
00:04:17.987 --> 00:04:20.235
and maybe it doesn't achieve the same feel-good
跟在 kiva.org 上借出100美元给别人买山羊相比，

61
00:04:20.235 --> 00:04:24.126
as giving a woman 100 dollars  to buy a goat on kiva.org,
这可能不会给你同样的感觉。

62
00:04:24.126 --> 00:04:28.051
perhaps supporting fewer, higher-impact entrepreneurs
向少数更具影响力的企业家提供帮助，

63
00:04:28.051 --> 00:04:31.024
to build massive businesses that scale pan-Africa
构建大规模的企业使其能够与泛非洲匹配，

64
00:04:31.024 --> 00:04:34.184
can help change this.
或许能够帮助我们改变现状。

65
00:04:34.184 --> 00:04:38.738
The political freedom for which our forebearers fought
我们先人为政治自由所作的拼搏

66
00:04:36.678 --> 00:04:42.236
is meaningless without economic freedom.
如果没有经济自由，就会变得徒劳。

67
00:04:43.146 --> 00:04:45.956
We hope to aid this fight for economic freedom
我们希望为争取经济自由出力，

68
00:04:45.956 --> 00:04:48.417
by building world-class businesses,
致力于打造世界级的企业，

69
00:04:48.417 --> 00:04:50.391
creating indigenous wealth,
创造本土财富，

70
00:04:50.391 --> 00:04:53.525
providing jobs that we so desperately need,
创造我们迫切需要的就业岗位。

71
00:04:53.525 --> 00:04:56.722
and hopefully helping achieve this.
与此同时也希望通过实现这些目标，

72
00:04:57.612 --> 00:05:00.514
Africa shall rise.
非洲会崛起。

73
00:05:00.514 --> 00:05:02.070
Thank you.
谢谢！

74
00:05:02.070 --> 00:05:07.828
(Applause)
（掌声）

75
00:05:09.291 --> 00:05:13.285
Tom Rielly: So Sangu, of course, this is strong rhetoric.
汤姆·赖利：桑谷，这是很强的比喻。

76
00:05:13.285 --> 00:05:16.280
You're making 100 percent contrast between microcredit
你说小额贷款与普通的投资手段以及

77
00:05:16.280 --> 00:05:20.645
and regular investment and growing regular investment.
不断增长的普通投资手段有天壤之别。

78
00:05:20.645 --> 00:05:23.097
Do you think there is a role for microcredit at all?
你认为小额贷款能否占一席之地？

79
00:05:23.097 --> 00:05:25.359
Sangu Delle: I think there is a role.
桑谷·德尔：我认为可以。

80
00:05:25.359 --> 00:05:27.913
Microcredit has been a great, innovative way
小额贷款一直是优秀创新的手段，

81
00:05:27.913 --> 00:05:31.883
to expand financial access to the bottom of the pyramid.
用于为向金字塔底层的人扩大金融活动的门槛。

82
00:05:31.883 --> 00:05:34.135
But for the problems we face in Africa,
然而，我们非洲目前所面临的问题，

83
00:05:34.135 --> 00:05:37.641
when we are looking at the Marshall Plan to revitalize war-torn Europe,
比如说，为振兴饱受战争蹂躏的欧洲而制定的马歇尔计划，

84
00:05:37.641 --> 00:05:39.724
it was not full of donations of sheep.
不只是单纯的捐赠羊群。

85
00:05:39.724 --> 00:05:41.446
We need more than just microcredit.
我们需要的不仅仅是小额贷款，

86
00:05:41.446 --> 00:05:43.577
We need more than just give 200 dollars.
也不是仅仅200美元的援助，

87
00:05:43.577 --> 00:05:46.651
We need to build big businesses, and we need jobs.
我们需要构建大规模的企业，需要更多的就业岗位。

88
00:05:46.651 --> 00:05:49.047
TR: Very good. Thank you so much.
赖利：非常好，感谢！

89
00:05:49.047 --> 00:05:51.712
(Applause)
(掌声）